				 Special unit for urology
 A STAFF REPORTER																								A Delhi-based urology treatment centre will set up a unit at AMRI Hospitals, Salt Lake.																								AMRI will provide the infrastructure and we will look after the diagnostic and treatment areas. We want to make the unit operational by January 2008, said Hanish Bansal, the executive director of RG Stone Urological Research Institute, which runs six urological hospitals in the country.																								Our facilities and human resources are on a par with internationally-renowned hospitals. Since we concentrate only on urology, we have to keep our units abreast of all recent innovations in the field, Bansal said.																								The treatment will be cost-effective and the recovery time minimal, he added.																								Expressing happiness over the arrangement with the Delhi-based institute, the executive director of AMRI Hospitals (Calcutta), D.N. Agarwal, said: The unit will be boon for hundreds of patients. 
